{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-12821/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-12821"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:28:21"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Woman in wedding dress stands by the door ominously"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-12821","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-12821"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/canvas/1/3fc2ce11-627a-4805-95fb-4970cc182881","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:16:41.926Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Upon returning to the chair and wall, someone has indeed appeared—his mother. Her appearance is precisely that seen in the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW69496221 BCX2\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-02009.html\"><u>photograph</u></a> of Mrs. Woodcock that Reynolds showed Alma on their first date. It remains unclear whether this is a representation of his imagination, a sickness-induced hallucination, or a ghost (phantom). In any case, it’s telling that Reynolds sees his mother in her wedding dress given that he has just completed the Belgian Princess’s wedding gown and that he’ll soon&nbsp;propose to Alma. He has been sorely missing his mother, and Alma will come to replace her, providing the maternal love and discipline that he desires.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12821/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:602.3376623376623,163.6363636363636,257.1428571428572,709.0909090909091"}}}]}]}]}